message.content:
This command is used to establish a secure connection (SSH) with a remote server on Amazon Web Services (AWS). The command contains several options and parameters:

1. `-i "~/UserKey.pem"`: Specifies the private key file that will be used for authentication. In this case, the key is located in the user's home directory and named "UserKey.pem".
2. `-C`: Enables compression of data (to improve performance).
3. `-L 25900:localhost:5900`: Specifies a port forwarding to establish a local port (25900) that forwards incoming connections to the remote server on port 5900 (VNC/X11 display protocol). This allows you to remotely access the graphical desktop of the EC2 instance using a VNC client on your local machine.
4. `user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com`: Specifies the remote user (user) and the hostname or IP address of the EC2 instance (ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com).

Overall, this command allows you to securely connect to a specific EC2 instance using your private key and port forwarding for accessing the remote graphical desktop.
